<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Evaluate/Prevention</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">Before calibrating the printheads make sure the filling procedure was successful, and no air is present in the printheads. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-D6D88FBC-5B55-4A7A-8E31-68C4E16557AC" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Background info</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">This calibration is used to set the correct PAINt-reference values so NFC will work correctly. A failure during this calibration is mainly caused when the nozzles are not filled correctly, and air is disturbing the jet-behaviour. 
